Package com.intellij.openapi.roots.impl

Class ModuleLibraryOrderEntryImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.roots.impl.ModuleLibraryOrderEntryImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Disposable, ExportableOrderEntry, ClonableOrderEntry, LibraryOrderEntry, LibraryOrSdkOrderEntry, OrderEntry, Synthetic, java.lang.Comparable<OrderEntry>

    public class ModuleLibraryOrderEntryImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements LibraryOrderEntry, ClonableOrderEntry
    Library entry for module ("in-place") libraries. This class isn't supposed to be used from plugins. Use OrderEntryUtil.isModuleLibraryOrderEntry(OrderEntry) to check whether an entry corresponds to a module-level library.

      • getFiles

        public VirtualFile [] getFiles(OrderRootType type)
        Description copied from interface: OrderEntry
        Returns list of root VirtualFiles of given type for this entry. Those files should be traversed in order they are returned in. Note that actual OrderEntry (as seen in UI) may also contain invalid roots. If you want to get list of all roots, use OrderEntry.getUrls(OrderRootType) method.
        Note that list of roots is project dependent.
        Specified by:
        getFiles in interface OrderEntry
        Parameters:
        type - required root type.
        Returns:
        list of virtual files.
        See Also:
        OrderEntry.getUrls(OrderRootType)
